				<br><b>Arithmetic cuts</b><br><br>
				The square with vertices (0,0), (0,4), (4,4), and (4,0) is divided in half by area by the line y=x. Find the y=mx+b form of the line which, along with y=x, divides the square into four regions with areas of precisely 1,3,5, and 7, as in the picture.<br>
	
