				<div><h2>Previous problem</h2></div>
				<br>
				<b>Lucky numbers</b><br>
				<br>On a lottery ticket, there are 5 distinct integers from 1 to 50 inclusive, in no particular order. Among the numbers on the ticket:<br><br>

The first number is the only perfect square.<br>
The second number is the only perfect cube.<br>
The third number is the only even number.<br>
The fourth number is the only prime number.<br>
The fifth number is the sum of the other four numbers.<br><br>

Determine the five numbers.<br>
